00:31:11,304 --> 00:31:12,261
but you enemies closer?

506
00:31:13,175 --> 00:31:14,263
You guys hosed me.

507
00:31:16,048 --> 00:31:18,093
DeSantos is the lynchpin
in our case

508
00:31:18,267 --> 00:31:20,095
against some very
dangerous people.

509
00:31:20,487 --> 00:31:21,705
We have an obligation
to his safety.

510
00:31:22,576 --> 00:31:24,012
To the safety of his wife,
and your child.

511
00:31:24,404 --> 00:31:25,492
My ex-wife,
they're not married.

512
00:31:28,843 --> 00:31:30,758
They were married two days
before they entered the program.

513
00:31:30,932 --> 00:31:34,588
It's, um, easier for the service
to relocate a family.

514
00:31:35,154 --> 00:31:36,155
What?

515
00:31:38,287 --> 00:31:39,245
You guys are worse
than I thought.

516
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:41,290
-Look, Jimmy.
-Don't "look, Jimmy" me.

517
00:31:42,683 --> 00:31:43,902
As far as I'm concerned,

518
00:31:44,076 --> 00:31:45,294
you guys are no better
than kidnappers.

519
00:31:45,860 --> 00:31:47,775
Now, look, Mr. Van Zandt,
I want to see my daughter.

520
00:31:48,167 --> 00:31:49,124
-You'll see her.
-When?

521
00:31:49,298 --> 00:31:50,996
-One weekend per month.
-What?

522
00:31:51,692 --> 00:31:53,259
You can't call her either,
Jimmy, she'll have to call you.

523
00:31:53,650 --> 00:31:55,391
Cases like this can drag on
for years.

524
00:31:55,870 --> 00:31:57,611
Now, I want the same deal
I got in the divorce,

525
00:31:57,785 --> 00:31:59,134
every weekend.

526
00:31:59,308 --> 00:32:00,396
What you ask is impossible,
I'm sorry.

527
00:32:00,831 --> 00:32:02,094
I'm not the criminal here!

528
00:32:02,268 --> 00:32:03,356
Jimmy, take it easy,
take it easy.

529
00:32:06,576 --> 00:32:08,404
I don't think
we've fully explored, uh,

530
00:32:08,927 --> 00:32:10,319
my client's options.

531
00:32:12,626 --> 00:32:13,975
JIMMY: You were a big help.

532
00:32:14,497 --> 00:32:16,021
Did you see that Van Zandt guy?
He's like dry ice.

533
00:32:18,327 --> 00:32:19,415
I want you to file
for full custody.

534
00:32:20,155 --> 00:32:21,200
Are you crazy?

535
00:32:21,940 --> 00:32:23,593
Even by some stroke of luck
I beat the guy.

536
00:32:23,767 --> 00:32:25,204
They don't have to comply
with a court order.

537
00:32:25,378 --> 00:32:26,335
-You heard them.
-Do it, Vinnie.

538
00:32:28,424 --> 00:32:29,948
-Congratulations.
-What for?

539
00:32:31,166 --> 00:32:32,689
I've never had a case
solve itself.

540
00:32:32,863 --> 00:32:34,169
What are you talking about?

541
00:32:34,343 --> 00:32:35,605
You hired me to find her,
she's found.

542
00:32:36,171 --> 00:32:36,911
-What's this?
-My bill.

543
00:32:37,433 --> 00:32:38,347
We're not through yet.

544
00:32:53,623 --> 00:32:56,365
Mr. Scranton?
I believe this is yours.

545
00:32:58,280 --> 00:32:59,586
What's this?

546
00:32:59,760 --> 00:33:01,327
It's a court order
to produce Jenny O'Meara

547
00:33:01,501 --> 00:33:02,719
for a hearing in seven days.

548
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:07,463
I don't have to accept this.

549
00:33:08,899 --> 00:33:09,944
The law says you do.

550
00:33:12,991 --> 00:33:15,819
[♪♪♪♪♪]

551
00:33:45,675 --> 00:33:46,415
Hey, you.

552
00:33:49,592 --> 00:33:50,637
I missed you.

553
00:33:51,377 --> 00:33:52,508
JENNY: I missed you, too, Daddy.

554
00:33:53,553 --> 00:33:54,423
Come here.

555
00:34:02,388 --> 00:34:03,519
Can we have a couple
of minutes alone?

556
00:34:03,693 --> 00:34:05,739
Absolutely not,
I have to supervise.

557
00:34:12,137 --> 00:34:13,181
I wanna come visit you.

558
00:34:14,008 --> 00:34:16,445
They said I can't talk
about where we live.

559
00:34:20,623 --> 00:34:21,450
How about school?

560
00:34:26,890 --> 00:34:27,935
Can I take a picture at least?

561
00:34:31,112 --> 00:34:33,680
VINCENT: Your Honor,
by not notifying Mr. O'Meara

562
00:34:33,854 --> 00:34:35,986
the moment that they placed
his child in the program,

563
00:34:37,205 --> 00:34:39,207
the government infringed on his
relationship with his daughter.

564
00:34:40,904 --> 00:34:43,037
My client, therefore,
is asking that full custody

565
00:34:43,211 --> 00:34:44,125
revert back to him.

566
00:34:44,299 --> 00:34:45,300
May I, Your Honor?

567
00:34:47,607 --> 00:34:49,261
The last thing
the US Attorney's office wants

568
00:34:49,435 --> 00:34:50,653
is to stand
between parent and child.

569
00:34:51,437 --> 00:34:52,742
We have offered Mr. O'Meara
a concession.

570
00:34:53,830 --> 00:34:55,267
They've offered him
one visit per month.

571
00:34:56,050 --> 00:34:58,879
The divorce agreement
was loosely worded,

572
00:34:59,053 --> 00:35:00,359
as Mr. Infante knows.

573
00:35:00,924 --> 00:35:01,969
He negotiated it.

574
00:35:03,144 --> 00:35:05,886
We simply cannot afford to move
Mr. O'Meara, his ex-wife

575
00:35:06,060 --> 00:35:08,193
and his daughter,
and two Marshall escorts.

576
00:35:09,107 --> 00:35:10,673
In this particular situation,
it would also impeach

577
00:35:10,847 --> 00:35:12,501
the security of the Witness
Protection Program.

578
00:35:13,937 --> 00:35:15,722
I've heard about all I need
to hear today.

579
00:35:16,766 --> 00:35:18,333
I am going to continue
this case,

580
00:35:18,507 --> 00:35:20,596
pending home
and psychiatric evaluations.

581
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,556
The social worker
was over my house.

582
00:35:23,991 --> 00:35:25,166
Went through my closets.

583
00:35:26,254 --> 00:35:27,864
Asked me if I watched
adult tapes.

584
00:35:28,169 --> 00:35:29,431
That sounds like
a social worker.

585
00:35:30,345 --> 00:35:31,477
I had the shrink on Wednesday.

586
00:35:32,869 --> 00:35:34,523
I keep seeing Jenny's face
in that courtroom.

587
00:35:35,829 --> 00:35:37,265
She was frightened, you know.

588
00:35:38,092 --> 00:35:39,659
I hate to put her through that.
It makes me sick.

589
00:35:40,790 --> 00:35:41,574
I told the shrink that.

590
00:35:43,053 --> 00:35:43,837
Piece of advice?

591
00:35:45,099 --> 00:35:46,144
Get a new lawyer.

592
00:35:47,057 --> 00:35:47,884
Vinnie's not very good, is he?

593
00:35:48,581 --> 00:35:49,538
I wanna see you win.

594
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:52,802
JUDGE POWERS: I am going to take 
this case under advisement.

595
00:35:53,499 --> 00:35:55,327
The participants
will be notified

596
00:35:55,501 --> 00:35:56,676
when I have reached my decision.

597
00:35:57,633 --> 00:35:58,547
All rise!

598
00:36:02,725 --> 00:36:04,074
JIMMY: This guy looks like
he's got one foot

599
00:36:04,249 --> 00:36:05,424
-in the grave.
-VINNIE: Don't say that, please.

600
00:36:05,902 --> 00:36:07,208
-Why not?
-I'm superstitious.

601
00:36:07,991 --> 00:36:09,123
What does that mean
under advisement?

602
00:36:09,950 --> 00:36:11,473
Now he's got the reports
from the social worker

603
00:36:11,647 --> 00:36:12,909
and the psychiatrist.

604
00:36:13,475 --> 00:36:14,737
He'll make up his mind,
that's it.

605
00:36:14,911 --> 00:36:16,609
-But how long?
-I don't know, a week.

606
00:36:18,219 --> 00:36:20,395
I don't know, maybe longer,
I don't know how long.

607
00:36:21,396 --> 00:36:23,268
JIMMY: You're killing me,
Vinnie, it's taking forever.

608
00:36:23,442 --> 00:36:24,312
VINCENT: Look what
I'm up against.

609
00:36:25,183 --> 00:36:26,923
Every two weeks,
regular as clockwork,

610
00:36:27,097 --> 00:36:28,534
I get papered by Van Zandt.

611
00:36:29,012 --> 00:36:30,971
He's got a staff that thinks up
ways to make my life miserable.

612
00:36:32,102 --> 00:36:34,627
New interrogatories,
amended actions.

613
00:36:34,975 --> 00:36:36,368
He wants to depose your mother.

614
00:36:36,542 --> 00:36:38,370
Every stalling tactic
in the book.

615
00:36:39,719 --> 00:36:41,199
So, he thinks I'm gonna win.

616
00:36:41,373 --> 00:36:42,678
No, that's not it at all.

617
00:36:42,852 --> 00:36:44,027
You're a pain in the butt.

618
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:46,595
They want to exhaust us.
Economically and emotionally.

619
00:36:46,769 --> 00:36:47,988
And you wanna know
something, Jimmy?

620
00:36:48,162 --> 00:36:50,164
It's working,
this case is killing me.

621
00:36:50,469 --> 00:36:52,035
My practice
is significantly off.

622
00:36:55,082 --> 00:36:56,388
We gotta bite, come on.

623
00:37:00,783 --> 00:37:04,439
-ALL: Trick or treat!
-Hey. There you go.

624
00:37:04,787 --> 00:37:06,398
Don't eat too much at once,
all right?

625
00:37:06,572 --> 00:37:07,660
All right.

626
00:37:07,964 --> 00:37:08,965
All right, good night.

627
00:37:09,314 --> 00:37:10,140
ALL: Good night.

628
00:37:11,229 --> 00:37:12,099
Be careful, now.

629
00:37:14,536 --> 00:37:15,450
Take the deal, Jimmy.

630
00:37:16,582 --> 00:37:17,583
Go see Jenny.

631
00:37:19,019 --> 00:37:20,673
Once a month is better than
what you got now.

632
00:37:23,502 --> 00:37:25,199
The longer he mixes it up
with the feds,

633
00:37:25,373 --> 00:37:27,419
the more scrambled
his brains become.

634
00:37:27,984 --> 00:37:29,769
Yeah, well,
put yourself in his shoes.

635
00:37:29,943 --> 00:37:32,772
I have, but he has
a business, too.

636
00:37:33,207 --> 00:37:34,904
He forgot to sign the check
for the beer distributor

637
00:37:35,078 --> 00:37:36,428
and they put us on the list.

638
00:37:36,906 --> 00:37:39,300
I had to go to the grocery store
to buy vodka for the bar.

639
00:37:39,474 --> 00:37:42,477
That's illegal,
my butt, his license.

640
00:37:43,435 --> 00:37:45,350
He doesn't know where
the quarterly tax forms are.

641
00:37:47,177 --> 00:37:48,483
I mean,
if he loses this place...

642
00:37:51,225 --> 00:37:52,487
Why don't you just talk to me
like you were here?

643
00:37:53,271 --> 00:37:54,097
JENNY: Okay.

644
00:37:55,055 --> 00:37:56,361
You got a boyfriend
at that new school?

645
00:37:57,275 --> 00:37:58,145
JENNY: Dad!

646
00:37:59,364 --> 00:38:00,626
Come on.

647
00:38:01,017 --> 00:38:02,671
JENNY: Tommy Higgins said 
he loves me.

648
00:38:03,846 --> 00:38:05,326
Is he as handsome
as you know who?

649
00:38:05,500 --> 00:38:06,719
JENNY: You're handsomer.

650
00:38:07,197 --> 00:38:09,461
He told two other girls 
he loved them, too.

651
00:38:09,635 --> 00:38:11,114
Well, stay away
from fickle boys.

652
00:38:11,985 --> 00:38:13,378
THERESA: That's enough, Jenny.

653
00:38:13,552 --> 00:38:14,683
JENNY: Mom says I have 
to hang up.

654
00:38:16,729 --> 00:38:17,817
Okay, honey, um.

655
00:38:20,210 --> 00:38:21,690
Listen, I love you, I miss you.

656
00:38:23,039 --> 00:38:24,737
Call me again, soon, okay?
Anytime.

657
00:38:25,651 --> 00:38:27,087
-JENNY: Bye, Dad.
-Sleep with angels.

658
00:38:28,175 --> 00:38:29,568
[LINE DROPS]

659
00:38:35,965 --> 00:38:37,445
JIMMY: She said "Y'all"
more than once

660
00:38:37,619 --> 00:38:39,273
on the telephone.
So she's someplace in the South.

661
00:38:40,230 --> 00:38:42,102
Enough about me,
let's talk about your daughter.

662
00:38:42,276 --> 00:38:44,104
Halloween, she dressed up
like a ballerina.

663
00:38:44,887 --> 00:38:47,063
Little girls love to dress up,
like, something pretty.

664
00:38:47,237 --> 00:38:48,717
Last year,
she was an Indian princess.

665
00:38:51,416 --> 00:38:52,417
-Let's dance.
-No.

666
00:38:53,635 --> 00:38:55,202
-Come on.
-No, I forgot how.

667
00:38:55,376 --> 00:38:56,595
It's like falling off a bike.

668
00:38:56,769 --> 00:38:58,640
Only more fun, oh, come on.

669
00:38:59,032 --> 00:39:02,775
-[♪♪♪♪♪]
-[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

670
00:39:36,635 --> 00:39:37,766
Is something happening
between us?

671
00:39:50,866 --> 00:39:51,824
You're beautiful, Liz.

672
00:39:53,391 --> 00:39:54,304
The timing stinks.

673
00:40:04,445 --> 00:40:06,012
VAN ZANDT: I expect
you've heard.

674
00:40:06,186 --> 00:40:07,883
Judge Powers has retired
from the bench, his health.

675
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:09,232
JIMMY: We
could have settled this.

676
00:40:09,711 --> 00:40:10,756
I'm in a war here.

677
00:40:11,757 --> 00:40:13,889
And if my agenda means
protecting a small fish

678
00:40:14,063 --> 00:40:16,152
like DeSantos in order to take
hardcore criminals

679
00:40:16,326 --> 00:40:17,676
and their drugs off the streets,
I'm going to do it.

680
00:40:18,154 --> 00:40:19,155
That's reality, Jimmy.

681
00:40:19,678 --> 00:40:20,896
My daughter's a casualty
of your war.

682
00:40:21,941 --> 00:40:23,333
And so am I.

683
00:40:23,769 --> 00:40:25,814
-This is counterproductive.
-Stay out of this, Vinnie.

684
00:40:27,076 --> 00:40:28,208
You're gonna do this to me
again, aren't you?

685
00:40:29,383 --> 00:40:30,950
You're gonna find another judge.

686
00:40:31,124 --> 00:40:32,081
You're gonna bury me
with a mountain of paperwork.

687
00:40:32,255 --> 00:40:33,082
Because you're bigger than me.

688
00:40:33,779 --> 00:40:34,910
Because you can.

689
00:40:35,084 --> 00:40:35,824
Because it's my job.

690
00:40:38,784 --> 00:40:40,525
Your job is gonna keep me

691
00:40:40,699 --> 00:40:41,830
from my daughter's
first communion.

692
00:40:42,744 --> 00:40:43,702
From her confirmation.

693
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:45,834
Your job stinks.

694
00:40:55,017 --> 00:40:56,192
The bastard is not going
to lie down.

695
00:41:00,240 --> 00:41:01,937
Hey, Ma. What do you think?
Wallet size.

696
00:41:02,677 --> 00:41:04,679
Oh, I love it.

697
00:41:05,854 --> 00:41:07,856
-Did Jenny call?
-No, not yet.

698
00:41:08,378 --> 00:41:10,119
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

699
00:41:10,293 --> 00:41:11,991
-Hello? Hey, Jenny.
-JENNY: Hi.

700
00:41:12,992 --> 00:41:14,341
Merry Christmas, Dad.

701
00:41:14,515 --> 00:41:15,951
Merry Christmas to you,
I love you.

702
00:41:16,125 --> 00:41:17,213
JENNY: I love you, too.

703
00:41:18,040 --> 00:41:19,433
What's the matter?
You sound kinda sad.

704
00:41:19,607 --> 00:41:20,390
-Did you get my presents?
-JENNY: Huh?

705
00:41:21,043 --> 00:41:22,392
Did you like
the cable car picture?

706
00:41:23,002 --> 00:41:24,090
JENNY: What cable car picture?

707
00:41:26,048 --> 00:41:27,180
Did you get
the cable car picture?

708
00:41:27,702 --> 00:41:29,487
JENNY: I didn't get 
any presents from you.

709
00:41:29,661 --> 00:41:30,836
What do you mean
you didn't get my presents?

710
00:41:31,010 --> 00:41:32,098
Let me talk to her.

711
00:41:36,494 --> 00:41:37,625
Hi, Jenny dear.

712
00:41:37,799 --> 00:41:39,105
JENNY: Merry Christmas.

713
00:41:39,279 --> 00:41:40,367
ROSE: Oh, Merry Christmas
to you, too.

714
00:41:51,726 --> 00:41:53,162
Vinnie, what's going on?

715
00:41:53,685 --> 00:41:56,296
I wanna know what's going on.
This Van Zandt, this machine.

716
00:41:56,601 --> 00:41:59,038
-I don't know what's going on.
-Day after Christmas, Jimmy.

717
00:41:59,517 --> 00:42:00,909
Gimme a second to gather myself.

718
00:42:02,737 --> 00:42:04,478
This guy is messing with me
and Jenny, directly.

719
00:42:04,652 --> 00:42:05,914
She didn't get any
of my Christmas gifts.

720
00:42:07,437 --> 00:42:09,701
-It's probably the mails.
-What do you mean, the mails?

721
00:42:10,092 --> 00:42:11,006
She didn't get
my Halloween card

722
00:42:11,180 --> 00:42:12,181
or any of the letters, okay?

723
00:42:12,355 --> 00:42:13,356
The mails?

724
00:42:14,009 --> 00:42:15,924
Jimmy, what do you want me
to do?

725
00:42:17,839 --> 00:42:18,927
What do you want me
to do?

726
00:42:19,885 --> 00:42:20,929
Tell them I give up.

727
00:42:22,017 --> 00:42:22,931
I want to see my daughter.

728
00:42:23,584 --> 00:42:24,629
Once a month?

729
00:42:25,064 --> 00:42:25,934
Once a month.

730
00:42:27,109 --> 00:42:27,936
That's better
than what I get now.

731
00:42:34,116 --> 00:42:37,946
[♪♪♪♪♪]

732
00:43:05,365 --> 00:43:06,975
Looks like your career
could use a boost.

733
00:43:08,237 --> 00:43:08,977
What do you want?

734
00:43:13,025 --> 00:43:13,982
Steer some cases your way.

735
00:43:16,245 --> 00:43:17,595
How'd I get to be so lucky?

736
00:43:20,075 --> 00:43:22,338
Looks like you could use
a new car.

737
00:43:24,166 --> 00:43:25,864
I bet your wife
could use a vacation.

738
00:43:26,299 --> 00:43:27,605
You wanna lay off
the furniture, please?

739
00:43:30,433 --> 00:43:32,827
All I'd have to do is screw up
Jimmy's case, is that it?

740
00:43:33,175 --> 00:43:34,960
That's not exactly
how I'd put it, councilor.

741
00:43:35,395 --> 00:43:36,309
How would you put it?

742
00:43:38,093 --> 00:43:40,008
Van Zandt's gonna eat you alive.

743
00:43:41,096 --> 00:43:42,315
The man doesn't lose.

744
00:43:43,577 --> 00:43:46,014
His staff is geared to take you
to the mat.

745
00:43:47,973 --> 00:43:51,106
You won't have time
for another client until 1995,

746
00:43:51,803 --> 00:43:53,935
and I don't think O'Meara's fees
are gonna stretch that far.

747
00:43:54,544 --> 00:43:55,589
Don't sugarcoat it.

748
00:43:57,591 --> 00:43:58,374
Get to the point.

749
00:44:00,768 --> 00:44:01,551
The point is economics.

750
00:44:04,816 --> 00:44:06,034
You understand economics,
don't you?

751
00:44:12,998 --> 00:44:14,303
You got your overnight pay?

752
00:44:14,477 --> 00:44:15,740
Well, it's important
you came with me.

753
00:44:15,914 --> 00:44:17,350
Yeah, I know,
but something came up.

