00:45:57,885 --> 00:45:59,060
MAN: Ticket, please.

783
00:46:03,064 --> 00:46:04,022
Thanks.

784
00:46:04,805 --> 00:46:05,850
Thank you.

785
00:46:07,416 --> 00:46:08,156
Come on.

786
00:46:14,554 --> 00:46:15,294
You're going to Denver.

787
00:46:16,991 --> 00:46:18,166
Be the last one off,
you'll be met.

788
00:46:19,994 --> 00:46:21,256
-Enjoy, Jimmy.
-Thanks.

789
00:46:29,177 --> 00:46:32,267
WOMAN: Flight 13 for El Paso 
is now boarding Gate 7A.

790
00:46:40,232 --> 00:46:42,277
Why don't you get a big sign
that says US Marshall on it?

791
00:46:44,236 --> 00:46:45,759
You know the drill?

792
00:46:45,933 --> 00:46:47,326
Yeah, I know, last one on,
last one off, I know.

793
00:46:47,979 --> 00:46:49,850
I know this is hard for you,
but it's safe this way.

794
00:46:50,677 --> 00:46:51,417
For everyone.

795
00:46:53,549 --> 00:46:57,510
[♪♪♪♪♪]

796
00:47:12,742 --> 00:47:13,831
You scare any children lately?

797
00:47:17,008 --> 00:47:20,707
[♪♪♪♪♪]

798
00:47:21,708 --> 00:47:26,191
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

799
00:47:40,031 --> 00:47:42,772
-[GARDEN SPRINKLER WHIRRING]
-[SIGHS]

800
00:47:45,950 --> 00:47:46,907
I'll go get her.

801
00:47:48,996 --> 00:47:53,000
[TRAIN HORN BLARING]

802
00:47:56,395 --> 00:47:57,265
You're a hard woman.

803
00:48:03,315 --> 00:48:05,839
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

804
00:48:31,169 --> 00:48:32,126
Go on.

805
00:48:37,784 --> 00:48:39,177
Hey, how you doing, huh?

806
00:48:39,960 --> 00:48:41,309
You all right? Okay.

807
00:48:42,571 --> 00:48:43,355
Look who came to see you.

808
00:48:46,967 --> 00:48:49,056
I had to come, Jimmy.
I couldn't let her fly alone.

809
00:48:49,448 --> 00:48:50,797
That's all right, Theresa.
I understand.

810
00:48:51,276 --> 00:48:52,581
Listen, I don't have
a lot of time

811
00:48:52,755 --> 00:48:54,105
and I'd like to spend it
with my daughter.

812
00:48:54,279 --> 00:48:55,758
So, you know, excuse me, please.

813
00:48:56,629 --> 00:49:00,328
[♪♪♪♪♪]

814
00:49:03,897 --> 00:49:05,986
ROOSEVELT: Uh, one of us needs
to be with you at all times.

815
00:49:06,900 --> 00:49:08,119
Take your pick.

816
00:49:11,426 --> 00:49:12,601
JENNY: Well, my teacher's okay.

817
00:49:13,733 --> 00:49:15,256
I like my old school better.

818
00:49:15,778 --> 00:49:17,389
They make fun of the way I talk,

819
00:49:17,955 --> 00:49:20,087
so I try to say ain't
and y'all like they do,

820
00:49:20,914 --> 00:49:22,350
but then mom gets mad.

821
00:49:25,919 --> 00:49:27,877
Grandma Rose says to tell you
that she loves you

822
00:49:28,052 --> 00:49:28,791
and misses you.

823
00:49:29,792 --> 00:49:31,142
Gina says the same thing.

824
00:49:32,795 --> 00:49:33,492
When you come to visit me,

825
00:49:34,754 --> 00:49:37,017
I got a brand new room
all fixed up for you.

826
00:49:37,800 --> 00:49:39,019
That's where Rose
has been sleeping.

827
00:49:41,195 --> 00:49:42,457
Excuse me.

828
00:49:42,762 --> 00:49:44,372
Can we go someplace
or is this house arrest?

829
00:49:46,418 --> 00:49:47,375
Oh.

830
00:49:48,420 --> 00:49:49,377
Be my guest.

831
00:50:15,490 --> 00:50:16,665
Want to go again?

832
00:50:16,839 --> 00:50:18,232
-Yeah!
-How about you, Roosevelt?

833
00:50:18,972 --> 00:50:20,147
I love my job.

834
00:50:21,714 --> 00:50:24,978
BOTH: I think I can,
I think I can, I think I can...

