♪ Then out came the rain... ♪

838
00:50:36,903 --> 00:50:40,689
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

839
00:50:56,531 --> 00:50:57,880
Hey, are we having fun?

840
00:50:58,490 --> 00:50:59,534
It's great!

841
00:51:00,100 --> 00:51:01,406
She got sick.

842
00:51:01,580 --> 00:51:03,408
Do you think we can find
a tamer ride?

843
00:51:03,582 --> 00:51:05,671
Oh, come on,
one more time, be a sport.

844
00:51:08,369 --> 00:51:09,414
I thought we'd never
get rid of her.

845
00:51:09,849 --> 00:51:10,589
Me, too.

846
00:51:11,981 --> 00:51:13,461
Sweetheart, do you like
where you live?

847
00:51:14,201 --> 00:51:15,159
It's okay.

848
00:51:17,378 --> 00:51:18,466
What do they call it?

849
00:51:22,601 --> 00:51:25,473
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

850
00:51:28,085 --> 00:51:29,521
JIMMY: You ever think about
having children, Roosevelt?

851
00:51:31,436 --> 00:51:32,480
I tell you, it's amazing.

852
00:51:34,003 --> 00:51:35,135
You know, sometimes, like today,

853
00:51:36,658 --> 00:51:37,920
you get to live
through their eyes.

854
00:51:39,792 --> 00:51:41,272
That's the selfish part
of parenting.

855
00:51:41,446 --> 00:51:42,751
And another times, like,
in the middle of the night

856
00:51:42,925 --> 00:51:43,839
they-- When they have a fever,

857
00:51:45,058 --> 00:51:46,451
no matter what you do,
you can't bring it down.

858
00:51:47,756 --> 00:51:49,323
I tell you,
there's no more helpless

859
00:51:49,497 --> 00:51:51,108
or scary feeling in the world.

860
00:51:53,371 --> 00:51:54,502
Either way, I wouldn't trade it.

861
00:51:57,114 --> 00:51:57,940
You should think about it.

862
00:52:03,772 --> 00:52:05,818
-Give Daddy a kiss.
-Daddy, please don't go.

863
00:52:08,342 --> 00:52:09,517
Come on, Roosevelt,
let her spend the night.

864
00:52:10,431 --> 00:52:11,998
Come on.
Theresa doesn't care.

865
00:52:12,172 --> 00:52:13,347
It's not gonna hurt anything.
call her.

866
00:52:13,782 --> 00:52:15,044
Time's up, Jimmy.

867
00:52:15,349 --> 00:52:16,872
You're just making it hard
on your child.

868
00:52:17,046 --> 00:52:18,396
And you know I can't
authorize that.

869
00:52:18,570 --> 00:52:19,527
I'll see you
in the morning, Jen.

870
00:52:20,485 --> 00:52:21,529
Sleep with angels.

871
00:52:38,242 --> 00:52:42,202
[♪♪♪♪♪]

872
00:52:47,425 --> 00:52:51,124
[CRICKETS CHIRPING]

873
00:53:08,010 --> 00:53:09,098
[WINDOW HINGE SQUEAKS]

874
00:53:15,453 --> 00:53:19,892
[♪♪♪♪♪]

875
00:53:35,516 --> 00:53:40,042
[♪♪♪♪♪]

876
00:54:02,935 --> 00:54:06,721
-[CRICKETS CHIRPING]
-[DOG BARKING]

877
00:54:43,280 --> 00:54:45,804
[LINE TRILLING]

878
00:54:51,070 --> 00:54:52,985
[DIAL TONE RINGING]

879
00:54:53,768 --> 00:54:55,161
-LIZ: Hello?
-Liz.

880
00:54:55,683 --> 00:54:57,729
LIZ: Who is this? Jimmy?

881
00:54:57,903 --> 00:54:59,687
Yeah, it's me. Listen,
I only have a couple of minutes.

882
00:54:59,861 --> 00:55:00,993
I saw Jenny alone.

883
00:55:01,341 --> 00:55:02,951
I know the city
where they moved her.

884
00:55:03,125 --> 00:55:05,127
Now, I need you to get
to the airport in Waco, Texas.

885
00:55:06,085 --> 00:55:09,784
[♪♪♪♪♪]

886
00:55:46,081 --> 00:55:48,301
[RINGING]

887
00:55:49,215 --> 00:55:49,998
LIZ: Hello?

888
00:55:51,260 --> 00:55:52,000
Jimmy?

889
00:55:53,132 --> 00:55:53,959
Who is this?

890
00:56:16,329 --> 00:56:17,983
JIMMY: How's my big girl? Huh?

891
00:56:20,289 --> 00:56:21,073
What's the matter?

892
00:56:21,900 --> 00:56:22,770
Do you feel all right?

893
00:56:24,598 --> 00:56:25,599
Sleep well?

894
00:56:28,602 --> 00:56:29,473
What are you talking about?

895
00:56:30,299 --> 00:56:32,214
That was a very dumb thing
you did last night.

896
00:56:35,174 --> 00:56:36,871
If you wanna get down on me,
wait until my daughter's gone.

897
00:56:37,219 --> 00:56:38,830
JENNY: She have to be
with us next time?

898
00:56:41,267 --> 00:56:42,094
I'm gonna miss you.

899
00:56:44,618 --> 00:56:45,750
Here, you keep her.

900
00:56:47,055 --> 00:56:49,580
Hey, okay.
I'll keep her until next time.

901
00:56:51,495 --> 00:56:52,278
Give me a kiss.

902
00:56:58,806 --> 00:57:00,155
All right, it's time to go.

903
00:57:02,462 --> 00:57:06,814
[♪♪♪♪♪]

904
00:57:28,880 --> 00:57:31,839
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

905
00:57:46,680 --> 00:57:47,855
You crawled out your window.

906
00:57:48,943 --> 00:57:49,857
You made a phone call.

907
00:57:52,425 --> 00:57:53,295
I went for a run.

908
00:57:55,123 --> 00:57:56,385
I sent a man by Liz Gallagher's.

909
00:57:57,386 --> 00:57:58,170
She wasn't home.

910
00:57:58,953 --> 00:57:59,911
Where'd she go?

911
00:58:00,520 --> 00:58:01,869
I don't know
what you're talking about.

912
00:58:02,566 --> 00:58:04,959
Phone records said it was a call
placed to her number from Texas.

913
00:58:12,967 --> 00:58:13,925
Look, what do you want me
to say?

914
00:58:15,927 --> 00:58:17,842
Come on, you're a father,
put yourself in my place.

915
00:58:19,408 --> 00:58:21,019
You should have seen the look
on my daughter's eyes.

916
00:58:21,193 --> 00:58:22,977
It was, like, I had done
something wrong.

917
00:58:23,891 --> 00:58:26,938
You were not to leave that room
except under supervision.

918
00:58:28,113 --> 00:58:30,028
You've violated the agreement
you signed.

919
00:58:31,246 --> 00:58:32,857
I think you wanted to find out
where she was

920
00:58:33,031 --> 00:58:34,119
so you could go back
and kidnap her.

921
00:58:36,513 --> 00:58:38,602
Hey, listen, I have every right
to know where my daughter lives.

922
00:58:39,864 --> 00:58:41,256
Where she goes to school.

923
00:58:41,561 --> 00:58:42,910
I have the right to know
if she's healthy,

924
00:58:43,781 --> 00:58:44,912
because I'm her father.

925
00:58:46,523 --> 00:58:47,959
Now, you government guys,

926
00:58:48,133 --> 00:58:49,482
I think sometimes
you forget your job is to serve.

927
00:58:50,265 --> 00:58:52,137
The agreement you signed
gives me the right

928
00:58:52,311 --> 00:58:53,355
to terminate your visit.

929
00:58:54,748 --> 00:58:55,793
How's that for rights?

930
00:58:56,794 --> 00:58:57,925
You can forget about
seeing that kid.

931
00:59:02,756 --> 00:59:03,583
Take your best shot.

932
00:59:29,478 --> 00:59:31,437
I want to remove DeSantos
and his family from the program.

933
00:59:32,656 --> 00:59:33,744
I can't do that.

934
00:59:34,048 --> 00:59:35,180
Besides, I'm not through
with them yet.

935
00:59:39,837 --> 00:59:40,968
You walk into a door?

936
00:59:44,189 --> 00:59:44,972
O'Meara?

937
00:59:49,934 --> 00:59:50,978
Who the hell does he think
he is?

938
00:59:52,110 --> 00:59:53,328
Do they know
you have Jenny's address?

939
00:59:53,720 --> 00:59:54,721
JIMMY: No.

940
00:59:55,592 --> 00:59:57,115
One of the marshals delivered
this to the club.

941
00:59:58,029 --> 00:59:58,986
It's from Theresa.

942
01:00:01,336 --> 01:00:02,642
"They said
they might move us, Jimmy.

943
01:00:03,556 --> 01:00:05,776
But I won't let them pull Jenny
out of another school.

944
01:00:06,994 --> 01:00:07,908
She just made new friends.

945
01:00:09,257 --> 01:00:10,519
It was good for her to see you.

946
01:00:11,651 --> 01:00:13,044
I don't know
when she can visit again.

947
01:00:14,611 --> 01:00:15,960
So I am writing to set
some things straight."

948
01:00:17,048 --> 01:00:18,353
THERESA: Bobby did a bad thing,

949
01:00:19,006 --> 01:00:20,007
but he is not a bad man.

950
01:00:21,095 --> 01:00:22,357
I love him,

951
01:00:22,531 --> 01:00:23,881
and we are trying hard 
to be a family

952
01:00:24,055 --> 01:00:25,360
during a difficult time.

953
01:00:26,448 --> 01:00:28,581
He has turned his life around.

954
01:00:28,886 --> 01:00:30,061
We go to church 
as a family now.

955
01:00:30,975 --> 01:00:31,976
He has a trade.

956
01:00:32,585 --> 01:00:34,021
And Jenny is beginning 
to warm to him.

957
01:00:35,066 --> 01:00:36,284
"I had a choice to make.

958
01:00:37,111 --> 01:00:38,025
I know what I did
broke your heart.

959
01:00:39,070 --> 01:00:40,201
Please don't hate me.

960
01:00:40,680 --> 01:00:41,681
Theresa."

961
01:00:45,250 --> 01:00:46,991
I can't hate her.
I can't even hate DeSantos.

962
01:00:48,383 --> 01:00:50,037
It was just Van Zandt
I was fighting at.

963
01:00:53,998 --> 01:00:55,608
What they're doing isn't working
and I can't think straight.

964
01:00:56,478 --> 01:00:57,741
I can't sleep through the night.

965
01:00:58,611 --> 01:01:00,221
I kept wondering
if what I'm doing isn't driving

966
01:01:00,395 --> 01:01:01,745
a wedge between Jenny
and me

967
01:01:01,919 --> 01:01:03,050
instead of bringing us
closer together.

968
01:01:04,399 --> 01:01:05,705
Second thoughts?

969
01:01:05,879 --> 01:01:08,055
Hell, yes,
second and third thoughts.

970
01:01:09,230 --> 01:01:10,579
They're rattling you, Jimmy.

971
01:01:11,015 --> 01:01:12,190
That's what they want.

972
01:01:12,364 --> 01:01:14,366
You're David
and they're Goliath.

973
01:01:15,019 --> 01:01:16,107
Yeah, but David had a weapon.

974
01:01:17,195 --> 01:01:19,066
He had a stone
and a thing to throw it with.

975
01:01:22,200 --> 01:01:24,071
So, you really like him?

976
01:01:25,464 --> 01:01:27,335
He got me right here.

977
01:01:29,163 --> 01:01:30,338
I'm worried about him though.

978
01:01:31,035 --> 01:01:32,906
Ever since his got back
from his trip,

979
01:01:33,080 --> 01:01:35,343
he's changed, he's distant.

980
01:01:35,517 --> 01:01:36,431
-GINA: Yeah, I know.
-Hi, Liz.

981
01:01:37,650 --> 01:01:39,565
-LIZ: Hi.
-Hey, Gina,

982
01:01:40,261 --> 01:01:41,262
has Vincent been in?

983
01:01:41,741 --> 01:01:43,264
Uh, not since you went away.

984
01:01:43,438 --> 01:01:45,571
Oh, he stopped by that Saturday,
had a couple of pops,

985
01:01:45,745 --> 01:01:48,574
got sloppy-sentimental,
and he paid off his tab.

986
01:01:48,879 --> 01:01:49,618
-Really?
-GINA: Yeah.

987
01:01:50,750 --> 01:01:52,099
It's like he dropped
off the face of the earth.

988
01:01:52,752 --> 01:01:54,362
I shoulda had some movement
on my case by now.

989
01:01:55,624 --> 01:01:56,930
Uh, maybe he got busy.

990
01:01:57,496 --> 01:01:59,498
Oh, Mick said
he saw him driving

991
01:01:59,672 --> 01:02:01,282
a new car down Broad.

992
01:02:01,630 --> 01:02:02,762
[SCOFFS] Do you believe that?

993
01:02:04,851 --> 01:02:05,852
Eight indicted.

994
01:02:06,723 --> 01:02:08,725
Eight gang members
going to Camp Uncle Sam.

995
01:02:09,987 --> 01:02:11,205
I'm accepting their pleas.

996
01:02:12,293 --> 01:02:13,773
You saying we didn't need
DeSantos after all?

997
01:02:14,818 --> 01:02:15,819
On the contrary,

998
01:02:16,341 --> 01:02:18,691
our leverage came
from one scared worm

999
01:02:18,865 --> 01:02:19,953
with a lot to lose.

1000
01:02:20,911 --> 01:02:22,173
We cut their little hearts
right out.

1001
01:02:24,131 --> 01:02:26,394
So let's put DeSantos
and family out to pasture.

1002
01:02:27,526 --> 01:02:28,353
We still need them.

1003
01:02:29,571 --> 01:02:31,356
Who's going to touch them,
they're all in jail.

1004
01:02:31,530 --> 01:02:33,227
Don't either of you forget
one thing, thank you.

1005
01:02:33,401 --> 01:02:34,446
As long as O'Meara's...

1006
01:02:36,535 --> 01:02:38,102
As long as O'Meara's case
is on the docket,

