if this is his best shot,

1227
01:17:51,362 --> 01:17:52,624
-he's in trouble.
-Yeah.

1228
01:17:53,233 --> 01:17:55,061
That is good news, Harrison.

1229
01:17:57,368 --> 01:17:59,022
You're going to have
your day in court, Jimmy.

1230
01:17:59,892 --> 01:18:02,025
Judge Manuel Ruiz
will hear your case.

1231
01:18:03,679 --> 01:18:05,332
Says here, you're going
to subpoena Vincent Infante.

1232
01:18:07,639 --> 01:18:08,422
Yeah, you got a problem
with that?

1233
01:18:09,380 --> 01:18:10,381
No.

1234
01:18:11,034 --> 01:18:11,948
Okay.

1235
01:18:13,427 --> 01:18:15,081
Let's get ready to rumble.

1236
01:18:18,519 --> 01:18:20,347
It is not our intention
to impede the relationship

1237
01:18:20,521 --> 01:18:21,740
between a father and a daughter.

1238
01:18:22,436 --> 01:18:24,177
No more than it is
to deny due process

1239
01:18:24,351 --> 01:18:25,352
or Constitutional rights.

1240
01:18:26,179 --> 01:18:28,355
Simply put,
this is not a simple case.

1241
01:18:29,966 --> 01:18:31,663
The issue is the custody
of Jenny O'Meara.

1242
01:18:33,099 --> 01:18:35,014
What we asking Your Honor
to answer for us

1243
01:18:35,188 --> 01:18:36,929
is one of the oldest questions
in law.

1244
01:18:38,104 --> 01:18:39,323
Is the right of the citizen

1245
01:18:39,497 --> 01:18:40,367
greater than the right
of society?

1246
01:18:43,240 --> 01:18:44,937
It is common in jurisdictions
all over the country

1247
01:18:45,808 --> 01:18:47,418
to grant immunity and protection

1248
01:18:48,419 --> 01:18:49,812
in order to prosecute
a greater menace.

1249
01:18:50,464 --> 01:18:51,378
Mr. O'Meara's case

1250
01:18:52,815 --> 01:18:54,077
makes a direct assault
on that policy.

1251
01:18:55,208 --> 01:18:57,471
In order to prosecute
this war,

1252
01:18:58,298 --> 01:19:00,126
society demands
swift and reasoned action.

1253
01:19:03,303 --> 01:19:04,391
My heart goes out
to Mr. O'Meara.

1254
01:19:06,959 --> 01:19:08,613
But it also goes out
to all those other parents

1255
01:19:08,787 --> 01:19:10,876
in this country, whose only hope

1256
01:19:11,485 --> 01:19:13,009
is for us to put away
the vermin

1257
01:19:13,183 --> 01:19:14,575
who deal drugs
to their children.

1258
01:19:21,800 --> 01:19:23,193
Would you like to address
the court, Mr. Cox?

1259
01:19:26,718 --> 01:19:29,155
I thought I'd give the court
time for the smoke to clear.

1260
01:19:29,765 --> 01:19:31,070
[LAUGHS]

1261
01:19:31,244 --> 01:19:32,724
The court will do
the editorializing,

1262
01:19:32,898 --> 01:19:33,725
Mr. Cox. Proceed.

1263
01:19:36,902 --> 01:19:37,729
I'll be brief.

1264
01:19:38,948 --> 01:19:41,254
Mr. Van Zandt said one thing
that I agree with.

1265
01:19:42,560 --> 01:19:44,867
This case is about the custody
of Jenny O'Meara.

1266
01:19:46,477 --> 01:19:48,479
We are not opposed
to protective custody,

1267
01:19:49,393 --> 01:19:51,264
but we are opposed
to the abuse of authority.

1268
01:19:52,352 --> 01:19:54,441
We want to fight drugs,
and crime families,

1269
01:19:55,312 --> 01:19:57,618
but we can do it
without a callousness

1270
01:19:57,793 --> 01:19:59,446
that isn't part
of our value system.

1271
01:20:00,839 --> 01:20:03,363
With Bobby DeSantos' help,
we were able to arrest

1272
01:20:03,537 --> 01:20:05,583
eight principles in a
60 million-dollar drug ring.

1273
01:20:06,540 --> 01:20:09,195
He wore recording devices
and provided important data

1274
01:20:09,369 --> 01:20:10,327
at great personal risk.

1275
01:20:12,329 --> 01:20:13,199
Thank you.

1276
01:20:17,334 --> 01:20:18,901
These were some
dangerous characters, sir,

1277
01:20:19,075 --> 01:20:20,206
-weren't they?
-BORELLI: Yes, sir.

1278
01:20:21,425 --> 01:20:22,774
Our bail must have been set
pretty high.

1279
01:20:22,948 --> 01:20:24,210
Were any of these suspects
able to meet it?

1280
01:20:24,863 --> 01:20:25,821
No, sir.

1281
01:20:26,952 --> 01:20:29,215
In fact,
all eight plea bargained

1282
01:20:29,389 --> 01:20:30,956
and are now serving time
in federal penitentiaries,

1283
01:20:31,130 --> 01:20:32,131
isn't that right?

1284
01:20:32,305 --> 01:20:33,829
BORELLI: That's correct.

1285
01:20:34,003 --> 01:20:35,831
So these dangerous criminals
haven't seen the streets

1286
01:20:36,005 --> 01:20:38,007
since their arrest,
and have been no direct threat

1287
01:20:38,181 --> 01:20:39,704
to DeSantos or his family.

1288
01:20:40,270 --> 01:20:41,445
Yes. But that's not the point.

1289
01:20:41,619 --> 01:20:42,838
Objection, Your Honor.

1290
01:20:43,012 --> 01:20:43,795
I'm through with this witness.

1291
01:20:45,579 --> 01:20:46,580
VAN ZANDT:
When were you married?

1292
01:20:47,320 --> 01:20:49,235
September 7th of last year.

1293
01:20:51,847 --> 01:20:52,586
Do you love your husband?

1294
01:20:55,285 --> 01:20:56,242
Yes.

1295
01:20:57,809 --> 01:20:58,592
VAN ZANDT: No further questions.

1296
01:21:00,290 --> 01:21:01,247
Go easy on her, huh.

1297
01:21:02,292 --> 01:21:03,249
VAN ZANDT: Your witness,
counselor.

1298
01:21:06,818 --> 01:21:08,124
Mrs. DeSantos,

1299
01:21:09,908 --> 01:21:11,170
when did you
and your family enter

1300
01:21:11,344 --> 01:21:12,476
the Witness Protection Program?

1301
01:21:13,825 --> 01:21:14,913
September 9th.

1302
01:21:16,393 --> 01:21:18,221
Two days after
your arranged marriage

1303
01:21:18,395 --> 01:21:19,396
to a known felon.

1304
01:21:19,875 --> 01:21:20,963
Object, Your Honor.

1305
01:21:21,441 --> 01:21:22,268
Sustained.

1306
01:21:24,923 --> 01:21:26,359
COX: Mrs. DeSantos,
did you believe

1307
01:21:26,533 --> 01:21:27,926
you would not be allowed
into the program

1308
01:21:28,100 --> 01:21:29,014
unless you were married?

1309
01:21:29,188 --> 01:21:30,494
That's what I was told.

1310
01:21:36,630 --> 01:21:38,241
COX: Let me be perfectly clear
about this.

1311
01:21:38,415 --> 01:21:39,851
Are you saying
that even if this court

1312
01:21:40,025 --> 01:21:41,287
should rule
in my client's favor,

1313
01:21:42,593 --> 01:21:44,290
you would refuse to comply
with that court order?

1314
01:21:52,168 --> 01:21:53,299
Mr. Scranton?

1315
01:21:57,303 --> 01:21:59,262
My office would not have
to accept that court order.

1316
01:22:00,132 --> 01:22:01,177
That's what I said.

1317
01:22:09,402 --> 01:22:10,316
You can't be in here!

1318
01:22:10,882 --> 01:22:11,970
Arrest me.

1319
01:22:22,633 --> 01:22:23,460
Hi.

1320
01:22:26,419 --> 01:22:27,943
-How you doing?
-Fine.

1321
01:22:28,726 --> 01:22:31,207
[♪♪♪♪♪]

1322
01:22:31,947 --> 01:22:33,339
-You all right?
-Yeah.

1323
01:22:38,736 --> 01:22:40,216
I just came in here
to tell you that I love you.

1324
01:22:42,174 --> 01:22:43,610
You're gonna get
in trouble, Daddy.

1325
01:22:43,915 --> 01:22:44,916
Yeah.

1326
01:22:48,180 --> 01:22:49,181
Give me a hug.

1327
01:22:54,186 --> 01:22:55,361
COX: Mr. Infante.

1328
01:22:56,754 --> 01:22:58,538
You are aware that your answers
could cause you

1329
01:22:58,712 --> 01:23:00,845
to be brought before the bar
on disciplinary charges?

1330
01:23:02,847 --> 01:23:03,587
Yeah.

1331
01:23:07,112 --> 01:23:08,940
I was approached
by Mr. Scranton

1332
01:23:10,507 --> 01:23:13,379
who offered to send cases
my way...

1333
01:23:16,295 --> 01:23:17,949
if I would stall Jimmy's case.

1334
01:23:19,864 --> 01:23:20,647
COX: To what end?

1335
01:23:24,825 --> 01:23:26,740
They thought they could make
Jimmy go away.

1336
01:23:30,744 --> 01:23:31,963
And did you stall?

1337
01:23:38,230 --> 01:23:39,188
Yeah.

1338
01:23:46,543 --> 01:23:49,459
Mr. O'Meara's
living arrangement is wholesome.

1339
01:23:50,199 --> 01:23:51,983
More than adequate
to raise his daughter.

1340
01:23:52,810 --> 01:23:55,726
I was sent by the court
in my capacity as a psychiatrist

1341
01:23:56,161 --> 01:23:58,729
to evaluate Mr. O'Meara's
fitness as a parent.

1342
01:23:59,860 --> 01:24:02,037
COX: Would you tell the court
the conclusion of your report?

1343
01:24:02,733 --> 01:24:04,822
It's my opinion
that the lifestyle created

1344
01:24:04,996 --> 01:24:06,389
by the Witness Program

1345
01:24:06,737 --> 01:24:08,782
could be extremely stressful
for the daughter,

1346
01:24:09,435 --> 01:24:10,871
and that she could not
be raised normally

1347
01:24:11,046 --> 01:24:12,395
in such an environment.

1348
01:24:12,960 --> 01:24:15,311
I recommend that Mr. O'Meara
be given custody.

1349
01:24:15,963 --> 01:24:17,574
He never missed
a visit with her.

1350
01:24:18,749 --> 01:24:20,751
When they took her away,
Jimmy changed.

1351
01:24:22,535 --> 01:24:24,363
You could see it
in everything he did.

1352
01:24:25,060 --> 01:24:26,539
VAN ZANDT: You don't like me,
do you, Mr. O'Meara?

1353
01:24:27,366 --> 01:24:28,280
What do you think?

1354
01:24:29,281 --> 01:24:30,456
And you've got quite a temper.

1355
01:24:33,111 --> 01:24:34,808
If you're talking about
why I hit your buddy over there,

1356
01:24:34,982 --> 01:24:36,201
I think you know.

1357
01:24:36,375 --> 01:24:37,115
Have you ever hit your daughter?

1358
01:24:37,724 --> 01:24:38,856
You bastard.

1359
01:24:39,422 --> 01:24:40,684
This court won't tolerate
that language.

1360
01:24:43,426 --> 01:24:44,557
Would you direct the witness,
Your Honor?

1361
01:24:44,862 --> 01:24:45,776
Your Honor, can I say something?

1362
01:24:47,386 --> 01:24:49,040
Answer Mr. Van Zandt's question.

1363
01:24:49,997 --> 01:24:52,174
Why should I have to answer
a question like that?

1364
01:24:53,000 --> 01:24:54,480
Because I can find you
in contempt.

1365
01:25:02,097 --> 01:25:03,315
I have never hit my daughter.

1366
01:25:04,011 --> 01:25:06,231
Mr. Van Zandt's baiting
my client.

1367
01:25:06,536 --> 01:25:07,928
Your Honor, can I just tell you
what happened?

1368
01:25:08,364 --> 01:25:09,278
I'm not through
with my questions.

1369
01:25:09,452 --> 01:25:10,757
Mr. Van Zandt,

1370
01:25:11,628 --> 01:25:14,021
the antagonism between you
and the petitioner

1371
01:25:14,196 --> 01:25:15,284
is counterproductive.

1372
01:25:16,067 --> 01:25:17,938
And your contempt for the power
of this lower court

1373
01:25:18,113 --> 01:25:19,201
is evident as well.

1374
01:25:19,592 --> 01:25:21,159
-Your Honor...
-Don't "Your Honor" me.

1375
01:25:22,291 --> 01:25:24,771
You know, I'm very disturbed
by Mr. Scranton's testimony

1376
01:25:24,945 --> 01:25:26,817
about not having
to abide by my ruling,

1377
01:25:27,513 --> 01:25:29,515
a position that you have
made clear that you support.

1378
01:25:32,518 --> 01:25:33,824
I am going to let
Mr. O'Meara speak.

1379
01:25:34,303 --> 01:25:35,869
Then I would ask
that the record reflect

1380
01:25:36,043 --> 01:25:37,262
my continues objection.

1381
01:25:37,436 --> 01:25:38,481
I'll note your objections.

1382
01:25:39,221 --> 01:25:40,047
Now sit down.

1383
01:25:51,450 --> 01:25:52,538
Welfare of my daughter...

1384
01:26:02,331 --> 01:26:03,158
I have this anger.

1385
01:26:07,118 --> 01:26:08,250
Excuse me.

1386
01:26:11,166 --> 01:26:12,210
The welfare of my daughter,

1387
01:26:14,560 --> 01:26:15,692
and my relationship to her

1388
01:26:15,866 --> 01:26:17,084
is the most important thing
to me.

1389
01:26:20,436 --> 01:26:22,002
A friend of mine once told me
I could win this case.

1390
01:26:23,917 --> 01:26:26,050
She said I could be David
beat Goliath.

1391
01:26:26,224 --> 01:26:28,008
And I said to her,
I said I don't have any weapon.

1392
01:26:28,183 --> 01:26:29,053
But I do, Your Honor.

1393
01:26:31,098 --> 01:26:33,013
It's a document that's hanging
in the corridor

1394
01:26:33,188 --> 01:26:33,927
of this building.

1395
01:26:34,450 --> 01:26:35,494
The Constitution.

1396
01:26:38,628 --> 01:26:40,499
Mr. Van Zandt says
he wants you to decide

1397
01:26:40,673 --> 01:26:42,022
between the rights of society

1398
01:26:42,197 --> 01:26:43,589
and the rights
of the individual so do I,

1399
01:26:45,765 --> 01:26:46,592
But the thing is...

1400
01:26:49,029 --> 01:26:50,205
these guys don't play fair.

1401
01:26:51,728 --> 01:26:53,730
He's harassed me with the IRS.

1402
01:26:54,426 --> 01:26:57,299
He tried to shut down my bar,
deprive me of my livelihood.

1403
01:26:58,474 --> 01:26:59,997
Corrupted my attorney.

1404
01:27:00,650 --> 01:27:02,478
I don't have to sit here
and listen to my office

1405
01:27:02,652 --> 01:27:04,219
-being assailed!
-These are the facts.

1406
01:27:05,176 --> 01:27:06,308
These are the facts.

1407
01:27:08,745 --> 01:27:10,094
These men have treated me
like I'm a criminal.

1408
01:27:11,356 --> 01:27:13,576
Confused
my daughter's affections.

1409
01:27:14,011 --> 01:27:16,100
-All right, Mr. O'Meara.
-For what? For what?

1410
01:27:17,580 --> 01:27:19,930
To protect a system
that destroys people's lives

1411
01:27:20,844 --> 01:27:22,585
so that this man can put
another notch on his gun?

1412
01:27:22,759 --> 01:27:24,587
Are you going to allow
this continue?

1413
01:27:24,761 --> 01:27:26,153
That's enough, Mr. O'Meara.

1414
01:27:26,458 --> 01:27:28,808
I want you to choose.
I want you to choose.

1415
01:27:28,982 --> 01:27:30,462
I want you to tell me
to my face

1416
01:27:30,854 --> 01:27:32,769
that what these people do
is the American way!

1417
01:27:33,160 --> 01:27:35,685
I gave you your chance.
Now, if you go any further

1418
01:27:35,859 --> 01:27:37,295
I'm gonna find you in contempt
in this court.

1419
01:27:37,469 --> 01:27:39,210
I don't care about contempt.

1420
01:27:39,732 --> 01:27:42,213
I want you to choose! Choose!

1421
01:27:46,739 --> 01:27:48,524
Why can't we live
near my father?

1422
01:27:49,307 --> 01:27:50,656
JUDGE RUIZ: That's what
we're trying to work out,
sweetheart.

1423
01:27:52,789 --> 01:27:54,094
He did something bad,
didn't he?

1424
01:27:54,399 --> 01:27:56,096
No. No, not at all.

1425
01:27:57,054 --> 01:27:58,098
He loves you very much.

1426
01:27:58,969 --> 01:27:59,970
I love him, too.

1427
01:28:00,362 --> 01:28:01,319
I know that.

1428
01:28:02,625 --> 01:28:03,539
Would you like
to live with him?

1429
01:28:06,193 --> 01:28:09,022
But what about my mother?
She'd be lonely without me.

1430
01:28:11,416 --> 01:28:12,374
I was so stupid.

1431
01:28:13,070 --> 01:28:14,550
I lost my temper,
maybe, my daughter.

1432
01:28:14,941 --> 01:28:16,639
The judge is a fair man.

1433
01:28:16,813 --> 01:28:17,640
He rescinded
the contempt charge.

1434
01:28:18,380 --> 01:28:19,772
I think he was moved.

1435
01:28:20,556 --> 01:28:21,818
I hope you're right
about the good guys winning.

1436
01:28:24,560 --> 01:28:25,517
MICK: Yo, Jimmy.

1437
01:28:30,740 --> 01:28:32,524
-Hello?
-COX: This is Cox.

1438
01:28:32,872 --> 01:28:34,831
-Get over to my office.
-I'm coming now.

1439
01:28:37,181 --> 01:28:38,008
[TELEPHONE CLATTERS]

1440
01:28:51,369 --> 01:28:52,370
You won.

1441
01:28:52,849 --> 01:28:54,720
-[COX LAUGHS]
-I don't get it.

1442
01:28:55,895 --> 01:28:56,940
Full custody.

1443
01:28:57,375 --> 01:28:58,507
You can pick Jenny up
from the marshal

1444
01:28:58,681 --> 01:28:59,725
tomorrow morning at 10:00.

1445
01:29:00,944 --> 01:29:02,162
What?

1446
01:29:02,337 --> 01:29:04,643
I'm stunned, that's all.
Just like that?

1447
01:29:04,817 --> 01:29:05,731
Just like that.

1448
01:29:07,864 --> 01:29:10,083
I don't know how to thank you.
And you.

1449
01:29:10,823 --> 01:29:12,172
Well, I'll tell you
how you can thank me.

1450
01:29:12,347 --> 01:29:13,870
You could buy me a drink
at that bar of yours.

1451
01:29:14,044 --> 01:29:15,611
-Let's go.
-Well, I got some paperwork

1452
01:29:15,785 --> 01:29:17,569
to finish up,
but, uh, I'll take a rain check.

1453
01:29:17,917 --> 01:29:18,744
[COX LAUGHS]

1454
01:29:20,920 --> 01:29:21,878
I know what time it is.

1455
01:29:22,400 --> 01:29:24,271
I want my full staff
in my office

1456
01:29:24,446 --> 01:29:25,577
and organized in one hour.

1457
01:29:26,926 --> 01:29:28,319
And while you're at it
find me an appellate judge

1458
01:29:28,493 --> 01:29:29,320
with a heart of stone.

1459
01:29:30,669 --> 01:29:31,670
Just do it!

1460
01:29:35,108 --> 01:29:36,240
Why don't you let it go?

1461
01:29:40,113 --> 01:29:41,332
I can arrange for you
to join Scranton,

1462
01:29:42,594 --> 01:29:44,117
playing checkers
while you baby-sit felons

1463
01:29:44,291 --> 01:29:45,380
in cheap motels.

1464
01:29:47,730 --> 01:29:48,687
I'm sorry.

1465
01:29:50,385 --> 01:29:51,690
I had a rare attack of humanity.

1466
01:29:59,219 --> 01:30:01,787
You fall into patterns.
Take life for granted.

1467
01:30:03,354 --> 01:30:04,877
Well, after today,
I can't do that anymore.

1468
01:30:06,183 --> 01:30:08,141
I wanna-- I wanna live my life.

1469
01:30:09,839 --> 01:30:10,796
I wanna...

1470
01:30:14,757 --> 01:30:15,671
What the hell is going on
over there?

1471
01:30:16,628 --> 01:30:17,629
Jimmy.

1472
01:30:27,639 --> 01:30:28,727
Damn that Van Zandt.

1473
01:30:39,085 --> 01:30:40,609
ALL: Surprise!

1474
01:30:40,783 --> 01:30:43,829
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

1475
01:30:44,003 --> 01:30:45,831
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1476
01:30:47,180 --> 01:30:48,138
Darling.

1477
01:30:51,446 --> 01:30:52,185
-Hey.
-GINA: So proud.

1478
01:30:58,540 --> 01:31:00,280
Congratulations, Jimmy.

1479
01:31:01,499 --> 01:31:05,634
[♪♪♪♪♪]

1480
01:31:07,244 --> 01:31:08,854
Took a lot of guts to do
what you did Vincent.

1481
01:31:11,378 --> 01:31:12,118
You're a good friend.

1482
01:31:14,425 --> 01:31:15,165
Thank you, Jimmy.

1483
01:31:16,035 --> 01:31:17,080
LIZ: Come here, you.

1484
01:31:17,254 --> 01:31:20,387
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1485
01:31:20,736 --> 01:31:21,998
GINA: Can I have your attention
everybody?

1486
01:31:22,477 --> 01:31:24,566
Hey, hey, hey, attention.

1487
01:31:25,262 --> 01:31:26,829
All right. Does everybody
have a glass of bubbly?

1488
01:31:27,003 --> 01:31:28,613
-ALL: Yes.
-GINA: Okay.

1489
01:31:29,179 --> 01:31:31,877
Okay, here's a toast
to the best dad we know

1490
01:31:32,661 --> 01:31:33,966
in the saloon business.

1491
01:31:34,140 --> 01:31:37,143
[ALL LAUGH] Hear, hear.

1492
01:31:40,756 --> 01:31:42,975
Hey, those are my glasses!

1493
01:31:43,149 --> 01:31:44,760
-Oh, you can get some more.
-Oh, you can get some more.

1494
01:31:44,934 --> 01:31:47,893
[ALL LAUGH]

1495
01:31:59,296 --> 01:32:00,210
[DOOR CLOSES]

1496
01:32:05,128 --> 01:32:06,433
They want us out
of the program now.

1497
01:32:07,696 --> 01:32:08,827
Too much publicity.

1498
01:32:10,263 --> 01:32:12,048
They say
we've breached security.

1499
01:32:13,528 --> 01:32:14,398
You're gonna be fine.

1500
01:32:15,921 --> 01:32:17,053
Those guys can't touch you
from jail.

1501
01:32:18,533 --> 01:32:19,925
Yeah. [SIGHS]

1502
01:32:24,626 --> 01:32:26,453
You know this wasn't about
taking Jenny away from you.

1503
01:32:28,325 --> 01:32:30,283
